56 /**************** Variables that are not populated by the config ********************
57 * files and need to be manually set for each test *
58 *************************************************************************************/
59 
60 /* Set which test to run */
61 uint32_t gTestNumber = 1;
62 
63 /*
64  -If this variable is set to zero, the number of frames given in the config files are not changed.
65  -If this variable is greater than zero, it will overwrite the configured number of frames for all tests run
66  with the value given here. This is useful if one wants to increase the test duration for tests with start/stop reconfig
67  without having to create new config files for all the reconfig.
68  */
69 uint16_t gNumberOfFrames = 0;
70 
71 /*If this variable is set to true, the test bench disables the features that are not supported on IWR devices.
72  Using this variable allows to run the same config file for AWR and IWR device. For AWR devices, set this to false.
73  The features not supported on IWR are:
74  - Periodic Digital and Analog Monitoring are not supported
75 */
76 bool gIwrDeviceFlag = false;
